Authorative thingamajig.


05 Jun 2015 20:18






Thank you to Delliott and Goomy for looking this over. Special thanks to qntm for inspiring and reviewing this.

Explanation.

Younothing.


The antimemetic part of the anomaly is that it's impossible to see and remember seeing the trees without a dose of mnestics in your system. This effect was caused by the antimemetic perception filter that the CC division applied. The weird  effect was the original effect from before they were hidden. The filter doesn't apply to painting of the trees (which is why there can be an image, they had an artistic D-Class do a painting after seeing the tree) but does apply to photos.

The Counterconceptual Division is a bit of mischief qntm and I cooked up. They serve the same basic purpose that the Antimemetic Department serves. Why do two divisions exist that do the same job? They can't remember each other.










